lnvAq0F9.title: Base of the Genesee Arch Bridge, Letchworth State Park
lnvAq0F9.description: A telephoto shot of the eastern base of the Genesee Arch Bridge (also known as the Portage Viaduct). The red steel arch extends beyond the frame. The base is embedded into an area likely excavated out of the gorge’s wall. Various stairs and catwalks line the sides of the base.
lnvAq0F9.lens: iPhone 16 Pro back triple camera 15.66mm f/2.8
lnvAq0F9.flash: Flash did not fire, compulsory flash mode

9S_9E3mC.title: Middle Falls, Letchworth State Park
9S_9E3mC.description: The Genesee River flows over the Middle Falls in Letchworth State Park. Trees on the bank of the river are turning to fall covers as the low sun illuminates them. In the foreground, several people stand on an overlook photographing the falls. One of them is somewhat precariously standing on a wet rock wall with a tripod.
9S_9E3mC.lens: iPhone 16 Pro back triple camera 6.765mm f/1.78

ogMP7Pbu.title: Upper Falls, Letchworth State Park
ogMP7Pbu.description: A waterfall in a gorge, surrounded by trees beginning to take on fall colors. The midday sun brightly lights the falls and the mist filling the gorge. A long train bridge spans the gorge over the falls.

Srq_na9c.title: <pixel-clock>
Srq_na9c.description: A screenshot of the <pixel-clock> demo. A square with a colorful background has 12 white pixelated dots in a circle, with 3 other dots inside. If it were a moving image, it would be obvious that the three inside dots correspond to an hour, minute, and second hands of a clock.

D-STK6Qy.title: <projectile-cannon>
D-STK6Qy.description: A screenshot of the projectile-cannon demo component. A black box contains 4 white squares of various sizes along the bottom edge. At the top of the box is 4 log lines corresponding to the coordinates of each square. Below the box are UI controls: X, Y, and Z sliders; and Fire and Clear buttons.

S7e9ZsqX.title: <sphere-shadow> and <sphere-shadow-wasm>
S7e9ZsqX.description: A screenshot of the sphere-shadow and sphere-shadow-wasm demo components. Two colorful boxes are side-by-side, both containing a pixelated oval. Under the sphere-shadow box is the text “Render time: 6.44 ms”. Under the sphere-shadow-wasm box is the text “Render time: 0.90 ms”. Underneath both is a “Resolution” selection menu, currently set at “50x50”.

wrbbesgD.title: <sphere-shadow>
wrbbesgD.description: A screenshot of the sphere-shadow demo component. A box with a colorful background contains a pixelated black circle, which is the rendering of a sphere’s shadow. Below it is the text “Render time: 17.26 ms”.

_Eh10XTl.title: Spiny Side Eye
_Eh10XTl.description: A low perspective telephoto side profile of a Desert Spiny Lizard as it sits on top of a small rock under a bush. Its eye looks to the far right.

1i3Fb4Wt.title: photos-page-2024-11-29

qhCg333k.title: Punk and Trash
qhCg333k.description: Close-up of a raw, rebellious piece of street art on a weathered blue wall. A black-and-white stencil of a square face with intense, smudged eyes stares out, its heavy eyeliner dripping like tears. Below it, graffiti in bold green and white reads “PUNK AND TRASH,” with an arrow pointing the way toward the entryway of the building — a worn blue metal door.

6yftaf4Z.description: A tilted black and white photo of the statue Major General Comte Jean de Rochambeau in Lafayette Square in Washington, D.C., across the street from the White House. Rochambeau stands above Lady Liberty, pointing ahead.

_felbJPu.title: Saguaro Bouquet
_felbJPu.description: A close-up photograph captures the white flowers of a saguaro cactus in full bloom. The large blooms feature delicate, layered petals that form ruffled cups around golden-yellow centers filled with visible stamens. Multiple flowers cluster together on the tall desert cactus, their creamy white petals catching the bright sunlight. Small insects can be seen on some of the blossoms. The contrast is notable between the soft petals of the flowers and the sturdy, ribbed surface of the saguaro that supports them. In the softly blurred background, more desert vegetation creates a backdrop of green tones.
_felbJPu.lens: iPhone 16 Pro back triple camera 6.765mm f/1.78
_felbJPu.flash: Flash did not fire, compulsory flash mode

BqdE9IcU.title: Saguaro Flower
BqdE9IcU.description: Close-up of a saguaro cactus flower in full bloom, showing delicate white petals surrounding a bright golden center filled with fuzzy stamens. The flower's white petals have subtle greenish-yellow edges, and behind it, the cylindrical cactus body is covered with clusters of tan-colored spines radiating outward. The image captures the striking contrast between the soft, ephemeral flower and the heavily armored desert plant it grows from.
BqdE9IcU.lens: iPhone 16 Pro back triple camera 6.765mm f/1.78
BqdE9IcU.flash: Flash did not fire, compulsory flash mode

qhlJFGxk.title: All Laced Up
qhlJFGxk.description: A wide-angle landscape photograph shows a large, leafless tree standing prominently in an arid desert environment. The tree's bare, gnarled branches extend in multiple directions against a clear sky, creating a stark silhouette. Numerous pairs of sneakers dangle from the branches by their laces, creating an unusual and striking visual element throughout the tree's canopy. The foreground features sandy, desert soil with sparse, low-growing desert vegetation and smaller shrubs scattered around the base of the tree. The background reveals a flat desert landscape with similar drought-tolerant vegetation extending to the horizon, where distant mountains or hills are faintly visible. A warm, muted filter has been applied to the photograph, giving the entire scene desaturated, earthy tones that emphasize browns, tans, and soft blues while reducing the overall contrast and creating a vintage, subdued aesthetic throughout the image.
qhlJFGxk.lens: iPhone 16 Pro back triple camera 6.765mm f/1.78
qhlJFGxk.flash: Flash did not fire, compulsory flash mode

6WFfZpjz.title: Split
6WFfZpjz.description: A wide-angle photograph captures a person using a large telescope inside an observatory dome at night. The image is bathed in red light, which preserves night vision for astronomical observations. Rebecca is positioned at the eyepiece of the Schulman 32-inch telescope at the University of Arizona's Mount Lemmon SkyCenter, her silhouette clearly defined against the illuminated equipment. The observatory's dome opening creates a natural frame that divides the composition, revealing a dark night sky with the moon visible as a bright white orb surrounded by scattered stars. The curved walls of the dome display a geometric pattern of panels, all tinted in the same red hue that dominates the scene. The telescope mount and mechanical components are clearly visible. The contrast between the warm red interior lighting and the cool darkness of the night sky beyond creates a clear separation between the controlled observatory environment and the vast cosmos being observed.
6WFfZpjz.lens: iPhone 16 Pro back triple camera 6.765mm f/1.78
6WFfZpjz.flash: Flash did not fire, compulsory flash mode
